snippet: The launching may inaugurate a new era for NASA in which private companies ferry people and supplies to the International Space Station.
abstract: Space Exploration Technologies--SpaceX, for short--launches its first commercial cargo flight to International Space Station, inaugurating new era for NASA in which private companies will take over transportation of people and supplies to low-Earth orbit.
lead_paragraph: The launching may inaugurate a new era for NASA in which private companies ferry people and supplies to the International Space Station.

headline.seo: SpaceX Sends Cargo-Carrying Rocket to Space Station
headline.main: Group Sends First Rocket Under Deal With NASA
